This paper proposes a new differentially-private decision forest algorithm that focuses on minimizing the number of queries required and the sensitivity of those queries. The paper discusses the use of the Exponential Mechanism and smooth sensitivity, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning and data privacy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
